      <p>The diagram editor edits diagrams. The diagram editor should not know about details of the application, e.g. that rectangles represent components and that circles represent ports. The diagram editor should allow drawing any kind of diagram.  Later phases can check the validity of a diagram, much like the phases of compilers for text languages.  Knowledge of the application should not be wound into the diagram editor. This is a <em>separation of concerns</em> issue.Â <a href="#fnref:1" class="reversefootnote" role="doc-backlink">&#8617;</a></p>
